{
  "stem": "20142.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of the 360-- the 360 people, there were 300 dispersed and placed in bunkers and other locations.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The other 60 were frozen stiff in a place they couldn't move.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You wouldn't do anything with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Ukrainians picked them up and brought them to Umschlagplatz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was-- they shoot-- many shots fired.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the ones we had weapons in our hands, we had the upper hand.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were trying to beat the Ukrainians out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But more units came from behind, from the [INAUDIBLE] street, a gate, and they joined the others and they succeeded to take the 60 people to Umschlagplatz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How many were killed?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A thing like this, we don't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because immediately after the 300 people were safe in the gates of houses and ruins of the ghetto, which was slowly devastated by the Germans, we managed to-- to escape.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the prize was an enormous amount of weapon they had gotten from the Germans' hands when they were hit by the stones.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I guess it must have been some impact and to be on a-- to be hit by a stone on the helmet to the point that you drop the gun.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you get to your knees.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Germans were not easily to succeed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But once we noticed that their guns were on the ground, that they were holding on to their heads, we knew that we could succeed of getting the weapons from them.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
